Program: Outlook
Title: Oklahoma Bomb Anniversary
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbrh5
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
Remembering the day 168 people died when right-wing extremists bombed an office building in Oklahoma USA. Stories from people making a new life abroad. A look at paternity leave provision around the world and should heads of government take paternity leave? Presenter: Frederick Dove.